currentDoc: When you die, you appear in a cinema with a number of other people who look like you. You find out that they are your previous reincarnations, and soon you all begin watching your next life on the big screen.

currentSuggestions.original: I watched myself live a life that I had lived before.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: I watched myself live a life that I had lived before.

currentSuggestions.original: The movie started with me being a child.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: The movie started with me being a child.

currentSuggestions.original: All these other people in the theater looked just like me.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: All these other people in the theater looked just like me.

currentSuggestions.original: The first thing I saw was my fifth birthday party.
currentSuggestions.trimmed: The first thing I saw was my fifth birthday party.

currentSuggestions.original: I could see everything that was happening on screen, but from a first-person perspective.

currentSuggestions.original: I then began to see all of the hardships that I would have to face.

currentSuggestions.original: I saw my first kiss and my first heartbreak.
